The paper introduces a Python library for deep probabilistic learning using Sum-Product Networks (SPNs). SPNs are a type of probabilistic graphical model, which are commonly used in machine learning for tasks such as classification, regression, and density estimation. Therefore, the most likely sub-category for this paper is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
